{
  "summary": "Add a visible privacy badge to index.html that surfaces the zero-tracking guarantee with a source-audit link",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "title": "Add privacy badge CSS styles",
      "description": "Add styles for a .privacy-badge component inside the existing <style> block. Style it as a small, non-intrusive banner below the tagline: subtle background (e.g. light green tint), small font, inline icon characters (no external icon fonts), flex layout for the three claim pills (no cookies · no tracking · no account), and a 'View Source' anchor. Include a @media (max-width: 480px) rule to stack or wrap the pills on narrow viewports."
    },
    {
      "title": "Add privacy badge HTML markup",
      "description": "Insert a <div class=\"privacy-badge\"> element in the .container, immediately after the .tagline paragraph. The badge must contain three visible claim tokens — '🔒 No cookies', '🚫 No tracking', '👤 No account required' — and a 'View Source' link using the view-source: protocol (view-source: + location.href rendered via a small inline script attribute or a static relative path) so users can inspect the full HTML in-browser and verify the zero-external-requests guarantee themselves."
    }
  ]
}
```

