{
  "summary": "Add a visible privacy badge below the tagline that communicates the zero-tracking guarantee with three claim pills and a View Source link for auditability",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "title": "Add privacy badge CSS styles",
      "description": "Inside the existing <style> block, add rules for .privacy-badge (light-green tint background, border, flex layout, small font), .privacy-pills (flex-wrap row for the three pills), .pill (dot separator via ::before pseudo-element on .pill + .pill), and .view-source (underlined, bold, matching green color). Include a @media (max-width: 480px) block that switches .privacy-badge to column layout and tightens pill gap for narrow viewports."
    },
    {
      "title": "Add privacy badge HTML markup with view-source link",
      "description": "Insert a <div class=\"privacy-badge\"> immediately after the .tagline <p> element. It must contain a <div class=\"privacy-pills\"> with three <span class=\"pill\"> tokens ('🔒 No cookies', '🚫 No tracking', '👤 No account required') and an <a class=\"view-source\" id=\"view-source-link\" href=\"#\">View Source</a> anchor. Follow it with a one-line inline <script> that sets document.getElementById('view-source-link').href = 'view-source:' + location.href so users can inspect the full source in-browser."
    }
  ]
}
